HEADWORD: Perstringe
<hw>Per*stringe"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>perstringere</ets>; <ets>per + stringere</ets> to bind up, to touch
upon.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To touch; to graze; to glance on.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To criticise; to touch upon.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Persuadable</ent>⟦br⟧
